What. A. Year. The Rutherford Group is closing the books on this year with 41 families served. To us; that means 41 stories we were able to be a part of. Stories like:
🍼 Helping a family celebrate the birth of their first baby the same week as buying their first home.
💍 Sharing the joy with newlyweds as starting their marriage with the dream of homeownership.
🪺 Helping empty nesters get their home ready to sell so they can downsize and start a new chapter together.
🍑 Welcoming families to Georgia and helping them find the perfect fit in a new place.
🥂 Seeing some familiar faces and working with clients who called us again to serve them for a second, third, fourth, and even fifth (!!!) transaction together.
.
🎉 Your home is not only your largest investment, it’s where your life happens. Where your story unfolds. THANK you, to our clients, for inviting us to play a small party in your story. It’s the greatest honor, and the best part of what we do.
.
We know that you likely know 10+ Realtors, and the fact that you chose us or referred your loved ones to us means the world. @allison.waldrip and I are aiming for bigger and better in 2023, and we hope that when you or someone you love is considering a purchase or sale, you’ll keep us in mind.

There are so many smiles and sweet memories to look back on from 2022. But boy, was it a roller coaster, too!
. 
We all measure success in our own way. 2022 is the year I got real clear on my version of success and happiness and made some big (sometimes difficult) changes to chase that down.
.
Sometimes we have to try new things & feel the heat in order to find ourselves refined on the other side of those experiences. 2022 was a year of refinement for me. The result is that today, I’m facing 2023 with vision, energy, and confidence in who I am, where I’m going, and who it’s all for. 
.
I hope you have a bright perspective on your year too, and if you don’t, I hope that you’ll be open to the uncomfortable process of refinement as well. 
.
Trust your gut, pursue excellence, and doors you never thought possible will open right before your eyes. I pray many blessings over your 2023, and hope our paths continue to cross.
.
📷: @laurenlcarnes

Have you met my partner in crime, life, and business, @allison.waldrip? Today is her birthday, so I thought it would be the perfect day to share our story and send her some love.
.
A couple years ago, I had three kids under 5 and a real estate business that was growing fast, fast, fast. I knew it was time to bring in another agent to help me serve my clients, but finding that right person was hard. I looked for six months until one day I got an email from a new agent that gave me pause. It was professional, well executed, and to be honest, I knew I was going to hire her before we even met. She totally pitched me and lawd knows I love a strong, confident woman to work with! Allison was teachable, had an amazing work ethic, and most importantly, she cared about her clients the way I do.
.
Fast forward a couple years, and Allison isn’t just my right hand, she’s my partner in this wild real estate business. If I were buying a house; I’d want Allison working on my behalf… and that’s The Rutherford Group promise. To treat our people the way we would want to be treated.
.
Happy Birthday, A. I’m so glad real estate brought you into my life. Here’s to working together and taking on the world (or, Atlanta, as it were).

Headlines lie, numbers don’t… and it’s important to understand that now more than ever, not all real estate markets are created equal. What’s happening here (in the southeast US) is the complete opposite of what’s happening on the west coast.
.
I love this graph from @wsj that illustrates the huge variance between the west coast and east coast markets. The top ten cities for growth are in, you guessed it, the south east! Why? Because our affordability, even with rising prices, is so much higher than on the west coast. With taxes, cost of living, and other factors taking place, thousands of Americans are fleeing California for sunny GA, which…makes demand higher, despite low inventory, and therefore keeps our prices going up up up.
.
Make sure you are talking to an agent who has expert knowledge of their market!
.
If you’re thinking about buying or selling this year, make sure to reach out and I’d love to grab coffee and discuss the market as well as your goals!

Ingredients:
- 1 lb ground beef
- 2 packages dry ranch dressing
- 1 package taco seasoning
- 1 can of rotel tomatoes
- 1 can diced tomatoes
*blend rotel and diced tomatoes for a smoother finish*
- 1 can shoe peg or yellow corn (don’t drain)
- 1 can black beans
- 1 can pinto beans 
- 1 can kidney beans (optional)
Instructions:
Brown the meat, drain the fat, and then add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 min.
Garnish with lime, avocado, Greek yogurt, and cheese. Laura will tell you she prefers mozzarella! 🧀
.
Pro tip - make your own taco seasoning by mixing the following: 1 tbls chili powder + 1 tsp cumin + 1 tsp garlic powder + 1 tsp paprika + 1/2 tsp oregano + 1/2 tsp onion powder + 1/4 tsp salt + 1/4 tsp pepper + 1/4 tsp red pepper flakes.
